# Sketch component conventions

## Structure

- React component that receives `isFullscreen = false` and uses it to size the canvas (e.g. full window when true).
- Use `@p5-wrapper/react`: `import { ReactP5Wrapper } from "@p5-wrapper/react";` and render `<ReactP5Wrapper sketch={sketch} />`.
- Import sketch layout styles: `import "./Sketch.css";` (all sketch files live in `src/sketches/`).

## p5 sketch function

- Signature: `const sketch = (p5) => { ... };` with `p5.setup`, `p5.draw`, and any helpers.
- In `setup`, create canvas with `p5.createCanvas(p5.windowWidth, p5.windowHeight)` (or use `isFullscreen` to decide dimensions). Call `p5.colorMode(p5.HSB)` (or other mode) if needed.
- Use `p5.windowResized` to resize canvas when the window resizes so fullscreen and non-fullscreen both work.

## Particle flow requirement

- The sketch must implement a **particle flow field**: particles following a flow field and/or forces (e.g. attraction/repulsion, mouse). No non-particle visuals as the main concept.

## Naming and export

- Component name: PascalCase (e.g. `ParticleFlow`, `ParticleFlowGen9`). Export as default.
- File name: match component name (e.g. `ParticleFlow.jsx`, `ParticleFlowGen9.jsx`).

## Reference

- Follow patterns from existing sketches in `src/sketches/ParticleFlow.jsx` and other `ParticleFlow*.jsx` files (flow field, particle class, `follow`/`update`/`show`).
